---
Nightblades are stealth-combat hybrids combining Assassin precision methodology with Warlock hex and shadow arts.
No formal guild or founding exists. The tradition emerged in margins between city-states where both traditions operated.
Core doctrine: strip the target's resistance before contact through ward dissolution, reflex disruption, and shadow reading.
Combat role is single-target elimination enhanced by hex-based debuffing and dual-strike capability.
Signature technique: two near-simultaneous precision strikes, the second exploiting the defensive shift caused by the first.
Key abilities include backstab, shadow reading, hex craft, and nightshade poison application.
Poison craft creates predictable degradation patterns used to time precision strikes.
Shadow-hex stripping and poison create independent degradation vectors harder to resist than either alone.
This is a remort class synthesizing Assassin and Warlock skill sets.
The tradition shifts assassination from reactive (waiting for openings) to proactive (manufacturing openings).
